{
  "doc_id": "26354",
  "text": "Several indirect methods are able to precisely estimate obesity, such as the total amount of body fat, as well as its distribution [CITATION_1] . While using computed tomography, dual-energy X-ray absorptiometry, and magnetic resonance imaging has a high sensitivity and specificity to diagnose obesity, using anthropometric indices such as body mass index (BMI), waistto-hip ratio (WHtR), waist circumference (WC), the waist-tohip ratio (WHpR), and the waist-to-height ratio (WHtR) are the simplest and the most cost-effective methods recommended in clinical practice and in epidemiological studies [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
